Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Pour the boiling @water{750%ml} for the risotto into a #medium saucepan{} on high heat. Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{20%g}, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to the lowest setting to keep warm.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the leek, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then cook until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Stir in the garlic and @Cajun spice mix{1}(add less if you don't like heat) and cook for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @risotto rice{175%g} and cook until translucent around the edges, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir a ladle of your stock into the rice pan. When the stock has been absorbed by the rice, stir in another ladle of stock.

Keep the pan on medium heat and continue stirring in the stock, letting it absorb each time.

The cooking time should take ~{20-25%minutes} and your risotto is done when your rice is 'al dente' - cooked through but with a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

== Lemon Crumb ==

Meanwhile, heat the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the crumb in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toast until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}, stirring frequently.

Once golden, stir in the lemon zest and transfer to a #bowl{}.

== Finishing ==

Once the risotto has ~{5%minutes} left to cook, stir in the @king prawns{300%g} and simmer for ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Remove from the heat and add the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and a knob of @?butter{1%knob}. Stir vigorously until well combined, then squeeze in some lemon juice.

Taste the risotto and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice if needed.

Spoon your prawn risotto into #bowls{} and top with the lemon crumb and spring onions.

Serve with any remaining lemon cut into wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!

> Step 5 MOD: If you've chosen to double up on king prawns, cook the recipe in the same way.